

compareTo() -- one of the methods of the Comparable Interface

Comparator() -- is an Interface that can be added under the main public execution class;
		used: 1. When the Comparable Interface is not implemented to a class created by a third party. 
			  2. When a different column, than what is already defined under compareTo(), needs to be sorted  
		
		1. Comparator is an interface that is defined using Anonymous class
			------------------------------------------------
			Comparator<clsName> com = new Comparator<clsName>(){
									public void Comparator(clsName L1, clsName L2){
									if (L1.getVar1() > L2.getVar1())
										return 1;
									else 
										return -1;
									}
								};
				Collections.sort(ar, com);				
								
								
		2. compareTo() method is implemented inside the class.
			------------------------------------------------
			public int compareTo(clsName obj){
				if(this.getVar2() > obj.getVar2)
					return 1;
				else
					return 2;
			}
			